    "content_hash": "10033a7015ed83ee",
    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "About Us\n\nFoundry Robotics is building an AI-first, assembly-focused contract manufacturer—software-defined manufacturing where robots and humans execute real production work.\n\nOur wedge isn’t just “models.” It’s the software layer that turns:\n\n - Orders → Schedules\n\n - Schedules → Work instructions\n\n - Work → Telemetry\n\n - Telemetry → Continuously improving throughput, quality, and cost\n\nThis role is not robotics engineering. It is for senior software engineers who build the cloud + on-prem systems that run the factory, and the data backbone that makes those systems observable, reliable, and scalable.\n\nWe are also hiring Robotics Research Engineers separately—this is a different role.\n\nThe Role\n\nWe are hiring a Senior Software Engineer (IC) to build the backend systems and infrastructure that power the factory of the future.\n\nYou will design and implement:\n\n - Cloud-based backend systems\n\n - On-prem factory services\n\n - Embedded-to-cloud data flows\n\n - Petabyte-scale visual data pipelines\n\n - Machine learning infrastructure across multiple compute environments\n\nYou will build production systems that stay online when factories are noisy, connectivity is imperfect, and downtime costs real money.\n\nThis is a hands-on engineering role. You will ship.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n - Cloud + On-Prem Architecture\n   \n   - Build and maintain a cloud-based backend for planning, scheduling, execution, inventory, traceability, and telemetry\n   \n   - Design multi-compute environment architectures spanning embedded, on-prem, and cloud systems\n   \n   - Implement infrastructure-as-code using Terraform\n   \n   - Ensure secure, reliable data movement between factory floor and cloud\n   \n   \n   ML INFRASTRUCTURE \u0026 DATA SYSTEMS\n   \n   - Build PB-scale visual data pipelines for ingesting, curating, indexing, and preparing manufacturing data\n   \n   - Design container orchestration and microservices architectures for ML infrastructure\n   \n   - Enable fine-tuning workflows and model deployment across hybrid compute environments\n   \n   - Implement workflow orchestration and data lifecycle management\n   \n   \n   RELIABILITY + PRODUCTION SYSTEMS\n   \n   - Design systems that tolerate intermittent connectivity and degraded network modes\n   \n   - Build observability: metrics, logging, tracing, runbooks\n   \n   - Make pragmatic tradeoffs between correctness, speed, and maintainability\n   \n   - Maintain high uptime in industrial production environments\n   \n   \n   FULL-STACK EXECUTION (WHEN NEEDED)\n   \n   - Implement APIs, services, database schemas, event-driven systems\n   \n   - Contribute to operator-facing tools and internal dashboards\n   \n   - Ship production-grade systems end-to-end\n\nWhat We’re Looking For\n\n - 3–6 years building and shipping real production software\n\n - Deep experience in backend systems and infrastructure, hybrid cloud + edge experience, infrastructure and DevOps, OR data at scale\n\n - Comfortable operating independently and owning complex systems end-to-end\n\n - Comfortable working at large scale (terabytes → petabytes)\n\nNice to Have\n\n - Experience supporting machine learning infrastructure in production\n\n - Experience in manufacturing, robotics, or industrial systems\n\n - Ability to obtain a government security clearance\n\n - Experience working on projects related to the Department of Defense (DoD)\n\nGrowth Opportunities\n\n - Help define the software backbone of an AI-native factory\n\n - Work across robotics, ML infrastructure, and industrial systems\n\n - Grow into larger technical ownership over time\n\n - Influence architecture and long-term system design\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\nThis is one of the only places where world-class manufacturing executives, mechanical engineers, robotics researchers, and software engineers sit in the same room building production systems together.\n\nWe are focused on reinventing manufacturing to be localized, autonomous, and software-defined.",
